  "text": "Alfaxalone is a neurosteroid anaesthetic available in Europe in a cyclodextrin 53 based formulation (Alfaxan, Jurox, Australia). It has excellent cardiovascular stability 54 [CITATION_1] ) and fast clearance from the body, making it suitable for repeated 55 dosing during anaesthesia [CITATION_2] ). Consequently, alfaxalone offers some 56 advantages over ketamine when it is used as part of a balanced anaesthetic protocol. 57",
